ref=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Sept 19, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104zpo1665702755304.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zpo1665702755304.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/zpo1665702755304.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"zpo1665702755304\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Java archive file <span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd.jar</span> contains the Uniface Java servlets—the Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) for deploying web applications and SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD) for SOAP-based web services.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__section_w5798ab1b5b1_w5799ab1b5_w5800ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d646995e53\">Description </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__p_d177431e1_d177432e1_d177433e1\">The Uniface servlets handle HTTP and SOAP requests received by the web server that need to be sent to Uniface.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__section_w5801ab1b5b3_w5802ab1b5_w5803ab1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d646995e62\">Checking the Version Number </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__p_d177437e1_d177438e1_d177439e1\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd.jar</span> file is updated with each Uniface release, and sometimes in patches and service packs. To check the version that you are using, you can do one of the following:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__li_d54335e1_d54336e1_d54337e1\">In a web browser, enter the URL for the\n               WRD_Version (for example:\n                  <code class=\"ph codeph\">http:localhost:8080/uniface/wrd/WRD_Version</code>). <p class=\"p\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__p_d177440e1_d177441e1_d177442e1\">If necessary, replace\n                     <code class=\"ph codeph\">localhost</code> with the host ID and <code class=\"ph codeph\">8080</code> with the\n                  port number of the web server in which the servlet is running.</p>\n</li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__li_d54338e1_d54339e1_d54340e1\">Extract and open the <span class=\"ph filepath\">manifest.mf</span> file in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd.jar</span>. By default, <span class=\"ph filepath\">wrd.jar</span> is located in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/tomcat/lib</span> directory of your Uniface installation.\n </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__section_a2t_cww_tcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d646995e107\">Updating the latest wrd.jar with patch 10.4.03 manually</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">For avoiding compatibility issues, the latest WRD module <code class=\"ph codeph\">wrd.jar</code> will\n            not be copied automatically in patching process. Users need to manually update it by\n            performing the following steps:</p>\n<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__ol_hv3_kww_tcc\">\n<li class=\"li\">Download the patch release 10.4.03.000 (or higher) and install it.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">If your Uniface installation folder name is, for example -\n               <dfn class=\"term\">UNIFACE_HOME</dfn>, and tomcat install folder is <dfn class=\"term\">TOMCAT_HOME</dfn> (by\n               default, it should be <span class=\"ph filepath\">UNIFACE_HOME\\common\\tomcat</span>):<ol class=\"ol\" id=\"zpo1665702755304__ol_ksb_sww_tcc\" type=\"a\">\n<li class=\"li\">If you have Tomcat 9 installed in <dfn class=\"term\">TOMCAT_HOME</dfn>,  copy\n                        <span class=\"ph filepath\">UNIFACE_HOME\\uniface\\webapps\\uniface\\WEB-INF\\lib_wrd\\v6\\wrd.jar</span>\n                     into <span class=\"ph filepath\">TOMCAT_HOME\\lib\\</span>.</li>\n<li class=\"li\">If you have Tomcat 10.1 installed in <dfn class=\"term\">TOMCAT_HOME</dfn>, copy\n                        <span class=\"ph filepath\">UNIFACE_HOME\\uniface\\webapps\\uniface\\WEB-INF\\lib_wrd\\v7\\wrd.jar</span>\n                     into <span class=\"ph filepath\">TOMCAT_HOME\\lib\\</span>.</li>\n</ol></li>\n</ol>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/rnm1665702667413.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD)</a><p>The Uniface SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD) is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering SOAP and WSDL requests for web services.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ctl1665702541086.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Web Request Dispatcher (WRD)</a><p>The Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) is used to deploy Uniface web applications. It is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering requests and maintaining connections between web servers and the Uniface Router. The WRD communicates with the Uniface Server via the Uniface Router.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534550\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534550\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "wrd.jar Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Sept 19, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 The Java archive file wrd.jar contains the Uniface Java servlets—the Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) for deploying web applications and SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD) for SOAP-based web services. Description The Uniface servlets handle HTTP and SOAP requests received by the web server that need to be sent to Uniface. Checking the Version Number The wrd.jar file is updated with each Uniface release, and sometimes in patches and service packs. To check the version that you are using, you can do one of the following: In a web browser, enter the URL for the WRD_Version (for example: http:localhost:8080/uniface/wrd/WRD_Version ). If necessary, replace localhost with the host ID and 8080 with the port number of the web server in which the servlet is running. Extract and open the manifest.mf file in the wrd.jar . By default, wrd.jar is located in the /common/tomcat/lib directory of your Uniface installation. Updating the latest wrd.jar with patch 10.4.03 manually For avoiding compatibility issues, the latest WRD module wrd.jar will not be copied automatically in patching process. Users need to manually update it by performing the following steps: Download the patch release 10.4.03.000 (or higher) and install it. If your Uniface installation folder name is, for example - UNIFACE_HOME , and tomcat install folder is TOMCAT_HOME (by default, it should be UNIFACE_HOME\\common\\tomcat ): If you have Tomcat 9 installed in TOMCAT_HOME , copy UNIFACE_HOME\\uniface\\webapps\\uniface\\WEB-INF\\lib_wrd\\v6\\wrd.jar into TOMCAT_HOME\\lib\\ . If you have Tomcat 10.1 installed in TOMCAT_HOME , copy UNIFACE_HOME\\uniface\\webapps\\uniface\\WEB-INF\\lib_wrd\\v7\\wrd.jar into TOMCAT_HOME\\lib\\ . Related Links SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD) The Uniface SOAP Request Dispatcher (SRD) is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering SOAP and WSDL requests for web services. Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) The Uniface Web Request Dispatcher (WRD) is used to deploy Uniface web applications. It is a Java servlet that is responsible for brokering requests and maintaining connections between web servers and the Uniface Router. The WRD communicates with the Uniface Server via the Uniface Router. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}